{{Infobox company | name = Anacomp | logo = Anacomp logo.png | type = [[Public company|Public]] | traded_as = {{OTCPink|ANCPA}} | foundation = 1968 | location_city = Chantilly, VA | location_country = USA | key_people = | industry = Computer services, document management | products = | revenue = | num_employees = | homepage = [http://www.anacomp.com www.anacomp.com] }}
'''Anacomp, Inc.''', is an [[United States|American]] company that specializes in computer services and document management. It was founded in [[Indianapolis, Indiana]], in 1968 by Ronald D. Palamare, Robert R. Sadaka, and J. Melvin Ebbert, three professors at [[Purdue University]].<ref name=EOI>{{Cite encyclopedia | editor-last=Bodenhamer | editor-first=David J. | editor2-last=Barrows | editor2-first=Robert G. | encyclopedia=The Encyclopedia of Indianapolis | publisher=Indiana University Press | year=1994 | isbn=0-253-31222-1 |page=261 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bg13QcMSsq8C&pg=PA261&lpg=PA261 |access-date=September 16, 2018}}</ref> Their goal was to direct the power of the computer toward the disciplines of investment management, education, urban analysis, computer science and civic systems, but is now headquartered in [[Chantilly, Virginia]]. The name Anacomp is a combination of the words ANAlyze and COMPute.<ref name=EOI /> Since its inception, Anacomp has made many acquisitions and spin-offs and has entered and exited different lines of business.
{{As of|2008}}, Anacomp's business is primarily in the service and document management sectors. In 2010, Anacomp sold off its CaseLogistix product line to Thomson Reuters.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://west.thomson.com/about/news/2010/07/13/tr-acquires-caselogistix.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-09-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203130050/http://west.thomson.com/about/news/2010/07/13/tr-acquires-caselogistix.aspx |archivedate=2010-12-03 |df= }}</ref> CaseLogistix is a document review application used by law firms for document review and subsequent case preparation.
