{{Infobox website | name = GCF Learn Free | logo = | logocaption = | url = <!-- {{URL|http://www.gcflearnfree.org}} --> | type = Online education/e-learning | language = English and Spanish {{URL|http://www.gcfaprendelibre.org}} | owner = Goodwill Industries of Eastern NC | creator = Rev. Dennis McLain | launch_date = <!-- {{Start date and age|2000|df=yes/no}} --> | alexa = 10,375 Global; 4,490 US (January 2014) }}
'''GCFLearnFree.org''' is a free online educational website focusing on [[technology]], job training, [[reading (process)|reading]], and [[math]] skills. The site is a program of [[Goodwill Industries]] of Eastern NC Inc. (GIENC) and the Goodwill Community Foundation Inc. (GCF). All content is created in [[Raleigh, North Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Who We Are |website=gcflearnfree.org |url=http://www.gcflearnfree.org/info/aboutus/who-we-are |accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref> GCFLearnFree.org has 16 employees responsible for content development and web development, and 9 online instructors who facilitate accredited classes by grading work and responding to learners' questions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Meet the Staff |website=gcflearnfree.org |url=http://www.gcflearnfree.org/info/aboutus/meet-the-staff |accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref>
==History== GCFLearnFree.org was created in July 2000 by GIENC president Dennis McLain as an online training program with both English and Spanish language lessons.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/triangle/stories/2010/02/22/focus11.html |title=2010 Legacy Leaders: Dennis McLain |date=22 February 2010 |website=Triangle Business Journal |page=1}}</ref> The program is funded through revenue generated from the value of donated items to Goodwill Community Foundation (GCF) throughout eastern North Carolina.<ref name="edsurge">{{cite web |url=https://www.edsurge.com/gcflearnfree |title=GCFLearnFree |date=19 March 2015 |website=EdSurge}}</ref>
==Self-paced tutorials== The GCFLearnFree.org programs are designed around [[self-paced instruction]]. The website offers dozens of free, self-paced tutorials in technology, Microsoft Office, work and career, reading, math, and everyday life.<ref name="edsurge" /><ref name="webjunction.org">{{cite web |url=http://www.webjunction.org/news/webjunction/learn-free-goodwill-community-foundation.html |title=Learn Free with the Goodwill Community Foundation |last1=Ferrari |first1=Ahniwa |date=22 July 2013 |website=WebJunction}}</ref> All tutorials can be accessed with no registration required, but users can also create a free GCFLearnFree.org account to track their learning history and create transcripts of completed tutorials.<ref name="northwestedtech.org">{{cite web |url=http://www.northwestedtech.org/2013_09_01_archive.html |title=Need training for 21st Century skills? |last1=Williams |first1=Sean |date=30 September 2013 |website=Northwest EdTech}}</ref> Tutorials use video, sound, art, storytelling, and text.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.edsurge.com/n/2014-10-10-10-ways-developers-can-help-adults-learn-to-read |title=10 Ways Developers Can Help Adults Learn to Read |last1=Segrè |first1=Francesca |date=10 October 2014 |website=EdSurge}}</ref> GCFLearnFree.org's self-paced tutorials are part of the free resources available at DigitalLiteracy.gov, an Obama administration initiative focused on digital literacy.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalliteracy.gov/resources |title=Digital Literacy Resources |website=DigitalLiteracy.gov |access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref> GCFLearnFree.org is also an Everyoneon.org partner. Organizations that use GCFLearnFree.org include K-12 schools,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sites.google.com/a/csd83.org/google-apps/home |title=Guide to Going Google |website=Tech Geeks 83 |access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref> colleges,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://libguides.rtc.edu/c.php?g=110011&p=713073 |title=ESL: Life and Work Skills - Websites |website=Renton Technical College |access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref> homeschool groups,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.plethorahomeschool.com/gcf-learn-free/ |title=GCF Learn Free - free videos and lessons in basic math and reading |date=7 November 2013 |website=Plethora Home School}}</ref> nonprofit organizations,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nmp.org/resources |title=Helpful Resources |website=NoMorePoverty |access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref> libraries,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.techsoupforlibraries.org/spotlight/positivity-and-patience |title=Positivity and Patience |last1=Anthony |first1=Jennifer |website=TechSoup for Libraries |access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref> businesses,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://us.walmartone.com/en/walmart/Education/2147495251/GCF-Learn-Free-Program/ |title=GCF Learn Free Program |website=WalmartOne |access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref> and career centers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goodtemps.org/training/ |title=Career Skills Training |website=GoodTemps |access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref>
==Online classes== GCFLearnFree.org offers free online classes that offer certificates of completion and continuing education units (CEUs).<ref name="webjunction.org"/> Online classes require registration and submission of assignments, and they are supported by online instructors.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.webwarehub.com/study-online-for-free-gcf-learnfree/ |title=Study Online For Free At GCF LearnFree |last1=Chauhan |first1=Saurabh |date=6 January 2013 |website=WebWareHub}}</ref> The online class program is accredited by the International Association for Continuing Education and Training (IACET).<ref name="northwestedtech.org"/>
==Awards and recognition== GCFLearnFree.org won the 2012 [[MERLOT]] Classics Award for its Word 2010 tutorial.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://olc.onlinelearningconsortium.org/conference/2012/et4online/2012-merlot-classics-award-word-2010-interactive-tutorial |title=2012 MERLOT Classics Award - Word 2010 Interactive Tutorial |website=Online Learning Consortium |access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref> [[GreatNonprofits]], a provider of user reviews about nonprofit organizations, named GCFLearnFree.org a 2014 Top-Rated Nonprofit based on reviews submitted by people who volunteer for or use the website.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://greatnonprofits.org/awards/browse/State:NC/Campaign:Year2014/Issue:All/Page:2 |title=Top-Rated Nonprofits in North Carolina |website=GreatNonprofits |page=2 |access-date=20 March 2015}}</ref> However, calling GCFLearnFree.org a "nonprofit" is not exactly accurate because the [[Employer Identification Number]] listed for GCFLearnFree.org by [[GreatNonprofits]] is registered with the [[Internal Revenue Service]] to Goodwill Community Foundation Inc. and not to GCFLearnFree.org,<ref>{{cite web|title=Exempt Organizations Select Check: 56-1954387 |website=irs.gov |url=https://apps.irs.gov/app/eos/pub78Search.do?ein1=561954387&names=&city=&state=All...&country=US&deductibility=all&dispatchMethod=searchCharities&submitName=Search |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20160630130303/https://apps.irs.gov/app/eos/pub78Search.do?ein1=561954387&names=&city=&state=All...&country=US&deductibility=all&dispatchMethod=searchCharities&submitName=Search |archivedate=30 June 2016 |accessdate=30 June 2015 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> and the name "GCFLearnFree.org" does not appear in other major nonprofit databases such as [[GuideStar]] and [[Charity Navigator]] but "Goodwill Community Foundation Inc." does.<ref>{{cite web |title=Organization Report: Goodwill Community Foundation, Inc. |publisher=[[GuideStar]] |website=guidestar.org |url=https://www.guidestar.org/profile/56-1954387 |accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Unrated Profile for Goodwill Community Foundation Inc. |publisher=[[Charity Navigator]] |website=charitynavigator.org |url=http://www.charitynavigator.org/index.cfm?bay=search.profile&ein=561954387 |accessdate=30 June 2015}}</ref>
