'''MDDL''', the Market Data Definition Language, is an [[XML]]-based messaging format for exchanging information related to # Financial Instruments # Corporate events related to the financial instruments # Market-related data
MDDL was developed by FISD (Financial Information Services Division) of SIIA (Software & Information Industry Association). The initiative for the use of XML in market data exchange was started in the year 2000 and has been gaining industry-wide acceptance.
